HEADWORD: Embrangle
<hw>Em*bran"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>em-</ets> (L. <ets>in</ets>) + <ets>brangle</ets>.]</ety> <def>To
confuse; to entangle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am lost and <qex>embrangled</qex> in inextricable
difficulties.</q> <rj><qau>Berkeley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

